113
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:16,360
that much.

114
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,620
You're unbelievable!

115
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:32,040
How could you do that to my friend?

116
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:32,970
You're too much!

117
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:40,920
I'll go and check on her.

118
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:42,000
Then I'm leaving now.

119
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:42,920
OK. Take care.

120
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,480
What's wrong?

121
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,850
Quarreled with Tang Can again?

122
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,240
I'm holding back

123
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,900
the most hurtful words to her.

124
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,520
It's very mature of you

125
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:19,960
to hold back the most hurtful words

126
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:21,640
when you're quarrelling with someone.

127
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:22,680
She's the oldest

128
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:23,760
among the three of us,

129
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:25,360
but she's not mature at all!

130
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,320
She always loses her temper with me

131
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:27,920
and she's the most immature!

132
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:31,040
But you still defended her just now.

133
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:41,290
I think there's one thing great

134
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:42,520
about Tang Can.

135
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:45,200
Pretty?

136
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,560
Simple-minded.

137
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,120
You can tell if she's happy or not

138
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:49,920
from her face.

139
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:51,760
She's straightforward.

140
00:06:52,159 --> 00:06:54,159
Is that really a compliment?

141
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:00,500
Hello, Mom.

142
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,120
It's in the transparent box

143
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:03,680
in the third drawer

144
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,540
in the hallway of the living room.

145
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:06,970
I've had dinner.

146
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:08,900
I was chatting with Jianjian.

147
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,520
Let me say a few words with Jianjian.

148
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:14,440
I don't think it's a good idea.

149
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:15,800
Why?

150
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:18,360
My mom wants to talk with you.

151
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:20,520
Hurry up.

152
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:25,800
Jianjian,

153
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,760
hello, this is Chen Ting.

154
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:30,200
Hello, Ma'am.

155
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:33,200
How are you?

156
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:34,600
I'm fine.

157
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:35,440
I can take care

158
00:07:35,440 --> 00:07:36,800
of myself now.

159
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,880
How is your father?

160
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,600
He's fine.

161
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,760
Thank you for asking.

162
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:44,560
I heard

163
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:45,159
that Ling Xiao

164
00:07:45,159 --> 00:07:46,880
rented an apartment opposite yours, right?

165
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,560
Since you can take care of each other now,

166
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,520
I'm relieved.

167
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:55,440
If there's nothing else, that's it.

168
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:57,440
See you next time. Bye!

169
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,520
Bye.

170
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:05,400
What made your mother change so much?

171
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:06,200
I don't know.

172
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,280
Maybe she has figured it out by herself.

173
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:10,680
I've thought about the problem

174
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,680
with your mother.

175
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:13,770
What do you mean?

176
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:16,000
Neither your mother nor your sister like me,

177
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,320
so if they know we're together,

178
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:19,320
they will definitely be against it.

179
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:21,240
If we tell them about our relationship,

180
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:21,680
it'll be like

181
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,200
Mars hitting the earth.

182
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:27,280
Do you care so much about their opinions?

183
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:29,520
It doesn't matter whether I care or not.

184
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,560
The important thing is

185
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:32,240
that it exists objectively.

186
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:35,960
I was worried

187
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:36,840
that you wouldn't think

188
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:37,840
about our future.

189
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:41,010
But it turned out you had thought so much about it.

190
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:44,720
By the way,

191
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,720
when did you start

192
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:52,180
